  "text": "• H 1 L (C, y α ) that solves (7.5), [CITATION_1] . In addition, u = u(·, 0) ∈ H s (Ω) solves (7.4) and we have the stability estimate We construct, as in § 5.2, a shape regular triangulation T Ω of Ω, which we extend to T Y ∈ T with the partition given in (5.6), with γ > 3/(1 − α). Following the proof of Theorem 5.4 we can also show the following error estimate. Theorem 7.1 (Error estimate for general operators). Let V T ∈ V(T Y ) be the solution of (7.8) and U TΩ ∈ U(T Ω ) be defined as in (4.5). If u, solution of (7.5), is such that Lu, ∂ y ∇u ∈ H 2 (y α , C), then we have",
